How to install and set up BlockSp for Visual Studio.
For BlockSp, version 1.0. As of March 2026.

Installation

(1) You can download BlockSp via
git clone https://github.com/BlockSp/BlockSp.git
or visit https://BlockSp.github.io

BlockSp is a header only C++ library with two external library dependencies.
Place the library folder where your compiler can find it.
Then include it in your code via #include "blocksp_include.hpp".

(1.1) You must also download the following two external libraries to run BlockSp:
	
	- Intel's Math Kernal Library (MKL) -- for dense/block linear algebra
			https://www.intel.com/content/www/us/en/developer/tools/oneapi/onemkl-download.html
	
	- blitz++ -- A high-performance matrix, vector, and multi-dimension array library.
			https://github.com/blitzpp/blitz

Tests for BlockSp and comparisons to the Eigen linear algebra library 
can be found in "blocksp_tests.hpp" and "blocksp_eigen_compare.hpp". 
Eigen comparisons require the installation of the Eigen library.
	https://libeigen.gitlab.io/

////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

Set up

Once the libraries are installed, we can now proceed to setting up your
Visual Studio environment. The majority of the work involves setting up MKL.

NOTE: BlockSp requires C++20 or later.
NOTE: make these changes to All Configurations, Platform x64

(2) Under project properties, navigate to VC++ directories
	(2.1) Add the following paths to Include Directories
	...\(blitz_location)\blitz-0.10 
	...\(MKL_location)\latest\include\
	...\(MKL_location)\latest\include\mkl\intel64
	...\(BlockSp_location)\BlockSp

	(2.2) Add the following to Library Directories
	...\(MKL location)\latest\lib

(2) Under project properties, go to the Linker 
(2.1) Add the following to Additional Dependencies
	...\(MKL_location)\latest\lib\mkl_intel_lp64.lib
	...\(MKL_location)\latest\lib\mkl_intel_thread.lib
	...\(MKL_location)\mkl\latest\lib\mkl_core.lib
	...\(oneAPI_location)\compiler\latest\lib\libiomp5md.lib

(2.2) Change the SubSystem to Console

(3) Under project properties, go to Debugging,
		Add the following to Environment:
			PATH=(oneAPI_location)\compiler\latest\bin;%PATH%
		Note: A restart may be required for after changing environment variables

(4) In the project settings
	(a) Turn off SDL checks
	(b) Change C++ Language Standard to /std:c++latest 
	(c) Turn off precompiled headers
	(d) Increase stack size from 1MB to at least 10MB. 

Note: (BlockSp_location), (blitz_location), (MKL_location), and (oneAPI_location) are
the path to your BlockSp, blitz++, MKL, and oneAPI folders, which you must find and provide.

